http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/Hospitals-told-to-give-details-of-biomedical-waste-segregation/article14006707.ece

Putting all the State-run and private hospitals located in Chennai district in a spot, the Southern Bench of the National Green Tribunal (NGT) on Monday directed them to produce their log books showing the month-wise segregation of biomedical waste.When a plea filed by Jawaharlal Shanmugam came up for hearing before the Bench comprising Justice P. Jyothimani and expert member R. Nagendran on Monday, the petitioner sought to know the details of the biomedical waste segregated in the 41 State-run hospitals and over 350 private hospitals within Chennai district.The Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board (TNPCB) submitted the list of private hospitals in Chennai district, which did not have the consent to operate.The Bench directed the hospitals in Chennai district to produce the details of segregation of biomedical waste from them and posted the matter for hearing on February 1.Alleging there was lack of liquid biomedical waste treatment facilities in hospitals, the petitioner sought a direction for corrective action from the TNPCB.During the hearing of the case earlier, the Bench directed the TNPCB to scrutinise the applications of government hospitals and medical college hospitals within a month for giving its consent after checking whether the biomedical waste disposal units are functioning as per norms.TNPCB submitted list of private hospitalsoperatingwithout consent